s with `excessive_print` issues that weren't auto-fixed:\n- `check_mb.py` (8 print statements)\n- `check_post.py` (4)\n- `find_post.py` (6)\n- `moltbook_post.py` (6 long lines)\n- `my_posts.py` (4)\n- `post_reply.py` (1 very long line at col 1243)\n- `run_on_paperspace.py` (8)\n- `test_tracer.py` (20)\n- `upload_and_run.py` (23 print + 3 long lines)\n- `verify_post.py` (4 long lines)\n- `vllm_latency_profiler.py` (24 print statements)\n\n**TODOs:** Only 1 found — in the self-improve script itself (`# Check for TODO/FIXME without owners`), which is expected.\n\n**No MEMORY.md update needed** — these were minor formatting/auto-fixes, no significant architectural or procedural changes."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5882,"output":626,"cacheRead":11757,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18265,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774252936398}}
